Mavericks’ Cuban Can’t Claim ‘Unclean Hands’ in Insider Case, Judge Rules

-- B y   T h o m   W e i d l i c h
-- 
2011-07-18T19:10:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/mavericks-cuban-can-t-claim-unclean-hands-in-insider-case-judge-rules.html
Mark Cuban , the billionaire owner of
the  Dallas Mavericks , can’t argue the U.S. Securities and
Exchange Commission’s insider-trading case against him is mostly
barred because the agency investigated him in an improper
manner, a judge ruled.  To contact the reporter on this story:
